    </div><section id="about">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>About PRN</h2>
    <p>PRN is a parent‑led network based in Churchill that supports families across Gippsland. We help parents impacted by child‑protection involvement with practical tools, rights‑based information, and trauma‑informed peer connection.</p>
    <div class="grid cards">
      <article class="card"><p class="kicker">What we do</p><p>Peer support circles. Meeting preparation. Letters and complaints guidance. Warm referrals to legal and counselling services. Constructive engagement with local agencies.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><p class="kicker">Who we support</p><p>Parents and kin with current or recent involvement who are working toward reunification or safer contact arrangements.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><p class="kicker">How we work</p><p>Confidential, respectful, and local. We centre lived experience and collaborate with existing services. We do not replace legal advice or provide case management.</p></article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="support">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Get Help</h2>
    <div class="grid cards">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Meeting prep</p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>Clarify goals and questions.</li>
          <li>Bring documents and a support person.</li>
          <li>Keep a written record afterwards.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Rights snapshot (Victoria)</p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>Request support or an advocate in meetings.</li>
          <li>Ask for decisions and reasons in writing.</li>
          <li>Use complaints and review pathways respectfully.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="kicker">Warm referrals</p>
        <p class="small">We connect you to legal aid, counselling, and local services. Email us for a current list.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

